--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
sharp / @img/sharp-libvips-*  (LGPL-3.0-or-later)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Image processing uses `sharp` (Apache-2.0), which dynamically links prebuilt
libvips binaries published as `@img/sharp-libvips-<platform>` under
LGPL-3.0-or-later. These are separate, dynamically-linked native libraries (not
statically compiled into Nodaro), which is compatible with redistribution. The
libvips source corresponding to those binaries is available from the sharp /
libvips projects: https://github.com/lovell/sharp and https://www.libvips.org

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
elkjs  (EPL-2.0)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The frontend graph auto-layout uses `elkjs`, a JavaScript port of the Eclipse
Layout Kernel, licensed under the Eclipse Public License 2.0. Source:
https://github.com/kieler/elkjs

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Binaries bundled in the Docker image
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The published Docker image installs Debian packages for `ffmpeg` (GPL-2.0+ /
LGPL-2.1+ depending on build configuration) and `aubio-tools` (GPL-3.0), plus
`yt-dlp` (Unlicense) and the Caddy web server (Apache-2.0). All are separate,
unmodified executables invoked as child processes — none is linked into
Nodaro's code, which remains under the licenses described above. Distributing
the image distributes those binaries; their corresponding source is available
from Debian (`apt-get source ffmpeg aubio` — https://www.debian.org), from
https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp, and from https://github.com/caddyserver/caddy.
The render worker additionally downloads Chrome Headless Shell (Chromium,
BSD-3-Clause and other licenses) via `@remotion/renderer`.

